U.S. September Index of Affluent Investor Confidence

-- B y   A l e x   T a n z i
-- 
2011-09-28T17:48:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/u-s-september-index-of-affluent-investor-confidence-table-.html
An index of affluent U.S. investor 
confidence rose last month, according to the Spectrem Group.  The index of affluent investor confidence rose to 
-16 in Sept. from a month earlier. The index of millionaire
investor confidence fell to -10 last month from -9. In 2010, the
Spectrem Group reported that the number of millionaires rose by
600,000 or, 8 percent, to 8.4 million households. Households with
a net worth, excluding the primary residence, of at least $5 million
rose 8 percent to 1,060,000 households. Households with at least 
$500,000 in investable assets rose to 13.5 million in 2010.  Following is a table compiled from the Spectrem Group index of
affluent investor confidence:   
